# Broken by Default

Formal verification study of security vulnerabilities in AI-generated code.

## Overview

This repository contains the artifacts for:

**"Broken by Default: A Formal Verification Study of Security Vulnerabilities in AI-Generated Code"**

We evaluate code generated by frontier LLMs and establish ground-truth exploitability using SMT-based formal verification (Z3), rather than pattern matching or heuristics.

## Key Results

- 64.8% mean vulnerability rate across models  
- 90 vulnerabilities formally proven exploitable using Z3  
- 0/90 detections by CodeQL (security-extended) on proven cases  
- Strong generation-review asymmetry (models detect issues they generate)

## Methodology

We model execution paths using Z3 (SMT solver) and derive constraint systems that demonstrate reachable invalid states (e.g. integer overflows, invariant violations).

All findings are backed by satisfiability witnesses.

